entry.title: Dianella callicarpa
entry.content: Growing in a damp area of sandy heath.

entry.title: Hypericum humifusum
entry.content: Note the small black dots on petals sepals and leaves, an identification feature.

entry.title: Parentucellia viscosa
entry.content: On a track in Annya SF. Now called Bellardia viscosa in Flora of Victoria.

entry.title: Unidentified
entry.content: A bracket fungus on fallen timber.

entry.title: Amyema pendula
entry.content: A set of four images. Growing on a melaleuca in a home garden but common in local bush nearby.

entry.title: Polygonum plebeium
entry.content: Small sprawling herb growing in mud of drying ephemeral wetland. Three images.

entry.title: Alternanthera denticulata s.s.
entry.content: Three images. Plants scrambling through reeds on the edge of a drying ephemeral swamp.

entry.title: Lythrum hyssopifolia
entry.content: Growing on the edge of a drying ephemeral wetland.

entry.title: Atriplex prostrata
entry.content: Growing on edge of ephemeral swamp. Two images.

entry.title: Sigesbeckia orientalis subsp. orientalis
entry.content: According to Flora Vic this is now just S. orientalis, and a native. This was growing on the edge of a drying swamp.

entry.title: Rorippa palustris
entry.content: Growing in drying ephemeral swamp. Identification suggested only.

entry.title: Boronia nana var. nana
entry.content: Late flowering record of this plant that grows in heathy woodland. Budj Bim NP . It normally flowers in spring.

entry.title: Monotoca scoparia
entry.content: Just starting to flower. Three images. Female flowers? Leaves distinctive.

entry.title: Lepidosperma longitudinale
entry.content: Three images showing male and female flowers a) anthers exerted and b) stigmas exerted. As well as the convex and twisted leaf.

entry.title: Cycnogeton alcockiae
entry.content: Triglochin possibly. It was growing in fresh water and the flower stalk was only about 15cm above water.

entry.title: Gratiola spp.
entry.content: Very small plants, growing in a damp spot. Possibly G. pubescens or G. peruviana.

entry.title: Mentha pulegium
entry.content: Small herb on the margin of Lake Condah.

entry.title: Selliera radicans
entry.content: Growing on the margin of Lake Condah on land exposed as water level receded over summer.

entry.title: Potentilla anserina
entry.content: Silverweed Argentina anserina has been recorded in Australia as Potentilla anserina, an alien species, but an article in Muelleria Vol 32 (2014) suggests it is an Australian species.

entry.title: Sisyrinchium iridifolium
entry.content: Sisyrinchium micranthum (Blue Pigroot), a weed on the roadside.

entry.title: Xanthorrhoea minor subsp. lutea
entry.content: Four images of the one plant.

entry.title: Banksia marginata
entry.content: In this area it can be prostrate in habit.

entry.title: Drosera peltata s.l.
entry.content: An insect trapped in the sticky leaf.
